=O_<?php exit; ?>a:1:{s:7:"content";O:8:"stdClass":24:{s:2:"ID";i:25293;s:11:"post_author";s:1:"1";s:9:"post_date";s:19:"2019-11-18 22:41:53";s:13:"post_date_gmt";s:19:"2019-11-19 03:41:53";s:12:"post_content";s:6361:"[vc_row][vc_column][vc_column_text]Today, the world’s leading universities are finding their places on social media, recognising that strong online presence is crucial for various marketing goals. Effective use of different social media platforms helps these universities better connect with prospective students, current students, alumni, faculty members and parents.

Technology and social media have come to play important roles in influencing the younger generation, so what better way to interact with stakeholders and target audience? Whether it is academics, athletics, research, or campus life, these universities below have played the social media game and unlocked quite a few achievements.

&nbsp;
<h2><strong>1. University of Michigan – Snapchat and Spotify</strong></h2>
username: uofmichigan

<img class="border alignnone wp-image-25299 size-full" src="https://xcaliburdigital.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/11/University_of_michigan_Snapchat.png" alt="" width="388" height="372" />

While many may question the university’s presence on Snapchat, the numbers on University of Michigan’s account don’t lie:
<ul>
 	<li>77% of its students use Snapchat daily</li>
 	<li>Within its first week, the account gained over 1,100 followers and received almost 800 snaps</li>
</ul>
With such tremendous support, the university aims to further connect with its students on a personal level by driving creative content on the channel.

&nbsp;

<a href="https://open.spotify.com/user/uofmichigan">open.spotify.com/user/uofmichigan</a>

<img class="border wp-image-25300 size-full alignnone" src="https://xcaliburdigital.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/11/University_of_michigan_spotify_1_out_of_2.png" alt="" width="1348" height="485" />

<img class="border wp-image-25301 size-full alignnone" src="https://xcaliburdigital.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/11/University_of_michigan_spotify_2_out_of_2.png" alt="" width="1343" height="481" />

As with their other social media platforms, University of Michigan plans out its content well. One of the few universities to use Spotify as a social media platform, this university has playlists for every mood a student may need. From summer vibes to moving in playlists, this university’s Spotify has got you covered.

<strong> </strong>
<h2><strong>2. Chamberlain College of Nursing – Pinterest </strong></h2>
<a href="http://www.pinterest.com/chamberlainedu/">www.pinterest.com/chamberlainedu/</a>

<img class="border wp-image-25295 size-full alignnone" src="https://xcaliburdigital.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/11/Chamberlain_College_of_Nursing_Pintrest.png" alt="" width="1342" height="620" />

Generating over 70 million active users and more than two billion monthly searches, Pinterest holds its own among the social networks. However, it’s often overlooked in social media marketing plans.

While time sensitive posts don’t do well on Pinterest, thanks to its “pin it” feature, well-crafted content can spread like wildfire, sending massive amounts of traffic to your website.

Chamberlain University’s College of Nursing used this to its advantage with creative boards such as “Nursing Graduation Cap Ideas” and “Apps for Nurses” that feature pictures of real nursing students. By posting content to help nurses navigate nursing school, it succeeded in humanising its programme and creating brand loyalists.

&nbsp;
<h2><strong>3. Harvard University – Instagram </strong></h2>
<a href="https://www.instagram.com/harvard/">https://www.instagram.com/harvard/</a>

<img class="border alignnone wp-image-25296 size-full" src="https://xcaliburdigital.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/11/Harvard_University_Instagram.png" alt="" width="525" height="615" />

Being one of the oldest and most renowned universities in the world, Harvard University utilises its various social media channels as a way to educate, inform and inspire.

With over 1.4 million followers on Instagram, Harvard University isn’t just known for its academic skill. They have one of the best university social feeds, demonstrating that with great intellect comes great creativity.

&nbsp;
<h2><strong>4. University of Cambridge – YouTube</strong></h2>
<a href="http://www.youtube.com/channel/UCc5vZEM1MLUzCrg_aZIJdeA">www.youtube.com/channel/UCc5vZEM1MLUzCrg_aZIJdeA</a>

<img class="border wp-image-25297 size-full alignnone" src="https://xcaliburdigital.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/11/University_of_Cambridge_YT.png" alt="" width="1326" height="614" />

Rather than a disingenuous attempt to shrug off its traditional persona in the digital world, University of Cambridge they’ve opted instead to use their historical reputation as a selling point. University of Cambridge uses YouTube to showcase its beautiful city, offering prospective students the opportunity to see what they could be a part of should they get in.

That’s not all, they make brilliant use of the platform to upload educational content. This not only generates traffic on its page, but it’s also a great way for potential applicants to understand the teaching style of the university as well as the standard of education they’ll get there.

<strong> </strong>
<h2><strong>5. University of Florida – Giphy</strong></h2>
<a href="https://giphy.com/uf">https://giphy.com/uf</a>

<img class="border alignnone wp-image-25298 size-full" src="https://xcaliburdigital.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/11/University_of_Florida_Giphy.png" alt="" width="358" height="532" />

The University of Florida has found an inspired way to get the attention of their students. With 1,100 uploads and over 1.8 billion views, the university has figured out how to fully take advantage of the GIF trend.

&nbsp;
<h2><strong>6. Boston University – Twitter</strong></h2>
<img class="border wp-image-25294 size-full alignnone" src="https://xcaliburdigital.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/11/Boston_University_twitter.png" alt="" width="912" height="588" />

Tweets with hashtags get twice as much engagement as those without – just don’t go overboard as research shows that when more than two hashtags are used, your engagement drops by 17%. Boston College has great hashtag game. It understands how to use hashtags and also capitalise on the latest trends.[/vc_column_text][/vc_column][/vc_row]";s:10:"post_title";s:69:"Universities that jumped on less conventional social media bandwagons";s:12:"post_excerpt";s:0:"";s:11:"post_status";s:7:"publish";s:14:"comment_status";s:4:"open";s:11:"ping_status";s:4:"open";s:13:"post_password";s:0:"";s:9:"post_name";s:69:"universities-that-jumped-on-less-conventional-social-media-bandwagons";s:7:"to_ping";s:0:"";s:6:"pinged";s:0:"";s:13:"post_modified";s:19:"2019-11-19 00:35:08";s:17:"post_modified_gmt";s:19:"2019-11-19 05:35:08";s:21:"post_content_filtered";s:0:"";s:11:"post_parent";i:0;s:4:"guid";s:36:"https://xcaliburdigital.com/?p=25293";s:10:"menu_order";i:0;s:9:"post_type";s:4:"post";s:14:"post_mime_type";s:0:"";s:13:"comment_count";s:1:"0";s:6:"filter";s:3:"raw";}}